{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254693/1930040801/0228.xml":{"full_text":"PARRISH TJILKS\nTOCLUBMEN\nAmos Parrish, internationally\nrecognized fashion expert and\n'business analyst, whose articles\n.appear daily in The Washington\n(Times, will today address local\nbusiness and advertising men at\na luncheon meeting of the Adver\ntising Club in the auditorium of\nthe National Press Club.\nHis vteit here as the guest of\nthe local club came at an oppor\ntune time, according to officers\nof the organization, in view of\nthe present business outlook.\nParrish is well-known to Wash\nington business leaders who on\nmany occasions have called upon\nhim for advice and analysis of\ntheir own business.\nHis talk will be on Fashion.\u201d\nbut will nbt follow any particular\nline of business but rather be a\ncross section of conditions in\nbusiness as a whole.\nbag stolen from lobby,\nThieves yesterday raided the\nklobby of the Tilden Hall Apart\nhnent, 3000 Tilden St. N. W., and\nleft with a suitcase of wearing\napparel worth $l5O, whicn be\nlonged to Charles V. Nicholas, of\nMontclair, N. J.\nUnderwriting\nr.\nin\nFIRE\n1 INSURANCE\nWho shall, or shall not, be meured; what\nproperty shall, or shall not, be covered; and\nwhat amount of insurance shall be accepted,\nif any? These are problems which daily face\nthe underwriter.\nFire insurance companies do not insure\n\u2022property, but do insure and safeguard the\ninterests of persons or corporations in\nproperty.\nThe property owner\u2019s character, financial\nability to possess and maintain the prop\nerty, the nsefnlnees of the property to its\nowner, his fire record, if any, and other\npertinent particulars, concern the under\nwriter.\nProperty to Be Covered\nThe type of property to be covered, be it\ndwelling, mercantile, manufacturing or per\nsonal property, as well as censtruction, oc\ncupancy, fire protection, exposure, damage*\nability, amount of insurance carried\ncompared with the value of the property,\nalong with many other conditions, must be\nstudied by the underwriter.\nThe underwriter is equipped with insur\nance maps, surveys, engineering data, con\nfidential character and financial reports,\nfire records, and other information upon\nwhich to base his judgment of a particular\nline of insurance.\nBroad Experience\nUnderwriters of Stock Fire Insurance com\npanies are men of broad experience who are\ncarefully trained in the selection of de\nsirable, and in the avoidance of undesirable,\nThe Underwriter renders an important\npublic service by endeavoring to avoid in\nsurance on risks that are likely to produce\nSegal or questionable claims and a conse\nquent effect on the cost of fire insurance.\nTM NATIONAL BOABB Os\nFINE UNBBRWBITBBS\nM Jobs Street, New Terk\naanonaL snaAveunew or\nSTOCK HM mOBRANCX\nbtasubxd m isss\nFORKCAST TILL BP. M. WEDNESDAY\nForth. District of Columbia.\u2014Fair\nand colder tonight; minimum tempera\nHire about 23 degree.; Wednesday fair;\nmoderate northwest wliids.\nFor Maryland\u2014Fair and colder to\nnight; Wednesday fair; freah to strong\nnorthwest wind., diminishing.\nFor Virginia\u2014Fair, colder In central\nand ea.f portion., tonight; light froet\nIn eaat and light to heavy in north\nand we.t portion.; Wedneaday fair;\nfre.h northweat and north wlnda.\nLOCAL TEMPERATURES\nYesterday I Today\n4 p. m. 4 a. m 44\np. m. 461 M a. tn......... 43\n,Mldnlght 4:,.N00n 44\ndeparture* from normal\nAccumulated excess of temperature\n,inee January 1. 1830, 333.\nExceaa of temperature since April 1,\nI*3o, 3.\nAccumulated deficiency of precipita\ntion since January 1. I*3o. 3 *3.\nExceaa of precipitation einee April 1.\nI*3o, 1.7*.\nTIDE TABLE*\nTodnv high tide. 3:36 a. m. and 4:06\n1,. _ Udes', 10:16 a. m. and\n10:6* P- m.'\nHigh tides, 4:40 a. m. and\n5:06 p. m.; low tides, 11:24 a. m. and\n11:66 p. m.\nTHE SUN AND MOON\nThe aun rose today, 5:35 a. m. and\n\u25a0eta, 8:30 p. m.\nThe aun riaea tomorrow, 5:34 a. Bl\n